summary: An Ordinance repealing Ordinance No. 23940, entitled "An Ordinance authorizing the Board of Public Works to execute a lease with the owners of blocks sixteen (16), seventeen (17), twenty-four (24) and twenty-five (25) of Hanford's Addition to South Seattle, by which said owners shall be permitted to occupy a certain portion of Tenth Avenue South, between Stevens and Hanford Streets, in exchange for a roadway across certain portions of blocks sixteen (16) and seventeen (17) in said Hanford's Addition", approved April 26, 1910.
